Enum KivaCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<KivaCommand>
      • KivaCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<KivaCommand>

    public enum KivaCommand
extends java.lang.Enum<KivaCommand>
    Enum that contains 5 possible actions for a Kiva robot to perform: move forward, left, right, take, or drop a pod. These values are specified by the user and enable the robot to move around the map.
    Version:
    4/5/2021
    Author:
    Kevin Phan

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DROP
      Kiva object will drop pod if current space is a valid drop zone.
      FORWARD
      Moves Kiva object one unit on either the x or y axis depending on direction Kiva is facing.
      TAKE
      Kiva object will take pod if current space contains pod.
      TURN_LEFT
      Turns Kiva object 90 degrees counter-clockwise.
      TURN_RIGHT
      Turns Kiva object 90 degrees clockwise.
